## 2. Embedded Documents

Embedded documents are POJOs nested inside a parent document. They do NOT get `@Document` —
that annotation registers a class as a top-level collection. Embedded classes are just Java objects.

```java
// LineItem lives inside Order.lineItems — no @Document
@Data
@Builder
public class LineItem {
    @Field("product_id")
    private String productId;

    private Integer qty;

    @Field("unit_price")
    private Double unitPrice;

    @Field("product_name")              // denormalized snapshot — intentional in MongoDB
    private String productName;
}

// ShippingAddress lives inside Order.shippingAddress — no @Document
@Data
@Builder
public class ShippingAddress {
    private String street;
    private String city;
    private String state;
    @Field("pin_code")
    private String pinCode;
    private String country;
}
```

**When to embed vs when to reference:**

- Embed: child is always fetched with parent, has no independent lifecycle, list is bounded
- Reference: child is updated independently, shared across many parents, list can grow without bound

