## 6. Aggregation Pipelines

Use `MongoTemplate.aggregate()` for grouped reports and cross-collection analytics.

```java
// Revenue report: orders joined with users, grouped by user, sorted by spend
public List<UserRevenueSummary> getUserRevenueSummary(LocalDateTime from, LocalDateTime to) {
    Aggregation agg = Aggregation.newAggregation(
        Aggregation.match(
            Criteria.where("order_status").is("COMPLETED")
                    .and("created_at").gte(from).lte(to)
        ),
        Aggregation.group("user_id")
            .count().as("orderCount")
            .sum("total_amount").as("totalRevenue"),
        Aggregation.lookup("users", "_id", "_id", "userDetails"),
        Aggregation.unwind("userDetails"),        // $lookup returns array — flatten it
        Aggregation.project()
            .and("userDetails.name").as("userName")
            .and("userDetails.email").as("userEmail")
            .andInclude("orderCount", "totalRevenue"),
        Aggregation.sort(Sort.by(Sort.Direction.DESC, "totalRevenue")),
        Aggregation.limit(20)
    );
    return mongoTemplate.aggregate(agg, "orders", UserRevenueSummary.class).getMappedResults();
}

// Top products: unwind embedded array, then group
public List<ProductSalesSummary> getTopProducts(int topN) {
    Aggregation agg = Aggregation.newAggregation(
        Aggregation.match(Criteria.where("order_status").is("COMPLETED")),
        Aggregation.unwind("line_items"),
        Aggregation.group("line_items.product_id")
            .sum("line_items.qty").as("totalQty")
            .sum(ArithmeticOperators.Multiply
                .valueOf("line_items.qty").multiplyBy("line_items.unit_price")
            ).as("totalRevenue"),
        Aggregation.sort(Sort.by(Sort.Direction.DESC, "totalRevenue")),
        Aggregation.limit(topN)
    );
    return mongoTemplate.aggregate(agg, "orders", ProductSalesSummary.class).getMappedResults();
}

// DTOs for aggregation results
public record UserRevenueSummary(String userName, String userEmail,
                                  Long orderCount, Double totalRevenue) {}
public record ProductSalesSummary(String id, Long totalQty, Double totalRevenue) {}
```

